                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d261">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">760D.61/1155: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Finland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grankulla</hi> (<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >Helsinki</hi>)</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1940-02-21T17:00:00+02:00">February 21, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 22—1:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>106. My telegram 95, February 16.<note n="63" xml:id="d261fn63">Not
                        printed.</note> Minister for Foreign Affairs informed me today Finnish
                    Government will not act for the present on Hungarian suggestion for mediation of
                    the conflict with Russia because there seems to be no reason to suppose such
                    action would be productive of favorable result at Moscow at this time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
